## Hub Layout (Anker 341, during streams)

| Hub Port | Connected Device | Cable |
|---|---|---|
| USB-C PD | Anker 100W GaN charger (wall) | USB-C to USB-C |
| USB-A (3.0) | Elgato Facecam MK.2 | USB-C to USB-A 3.0 — **must be USB 3.0** for uncompressed 1080p60 |
| USB-A (3.0) | Blue Yeti Nano | Micro-USB to USB-A — USB 2.0 sufficient |
| USB-A (3.0) | ZenScreen MB16ACV | USB-C to USB-A — DisplayLink driver required |
| USB-A (3.0) | Elgato Stream Deck + | USB-C to USB-A |

> ⚠️ Hub does NOT support DP Alt Mode — ZenScreen must use USB-A + DisplayLink, not USB-C.
> ⚠️ Hub HDMI is 4K@30Hz only and not currently in use.

---

## Cable Reference

### Elgato Facecam MK.2
| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Connector at camera** | USB-C |
| **Connector at hub** | USB-A |
| **Required standard** | USB 3.0 (5 Gbps) minimum — **non-negotiable for uncompressed output** |
| **USB 2.0 behavior** | Falls back to MJPEG compressed — silent quality downgrade, no error shown |
| **Included cable** | USB-C to USB-A, 2m, braided |
| **Max safe length** | 3m (passive) |

### ASUS ZenScreen MB16ACV
| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Connector at monitor** | USB-C |
| **Current connection method** | USB-C to USB-A → hub USB-A port → DisplayLink driver |
| **Required standard** | USB 3.0 for DisplayLink mode |
| **Driver required** | Yes — DisplayLink, already installed ✅ |
| **Alternative (not currently used)** | USB-C direct to laptop USB-C port (DP Alt Mode, no driver needed) — takes only USB-C port |
| **Included cables** | USB-C to USB-C (~1m) + USB-C to USB-A (~1m) |

### Blue Yeti Nano
| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Connector at mic** | **Micro-USB** (not Mini-USB — common mistake) |
| **Connector at hub** | USB-A |
| **Required standard** | USB 2.0 — fully sufficient for 24-bit/48kHz audio |
| **Must be** | Data + charge cable — charge-only cables won't transmit audio |
| **Included cable** | Micro-USB to USB-A, ~6ft, with ferrite choke |
| **Max practical length** | ~3m before electrical noise risk |

